(5. THE SCHEME BENEATH) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Scheme is the implementation language, not the user interface. The) show newline
(novice sees a shell; the schemer sees a REPL. Same system, different) show newline
(lenses.) show newline
() show newline
(By default, Scheme internals are hidden:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Inspector disabled - errors show simple messages, not debug> prompts) show newline
(  * Exception display uses plain language, not 'unbound variable') show newline
(  * Help shows commands, not S-expressions) show newline
(  * The : prompt is a portal, not a lambda) show newline
() show newline
(Schemers opt in with \(enable-inspector!\) and see the machinery. The) show newline
(abstraction layer is permeable but not transparent.) show newline
() show newline
(This is not dumbing down. It is layered revelation - the same principle) show newline
(that makes Cyberspace.app feel native on Mac while running pure Scheme) show newline
(underneath.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
